[ASF virus may have spread widely during the 5 weeks that elapsed between being initially suspected in Luzon (5 Jul 2019) and the date of its eventual confirmation, 30 Aug 2019. The efforts to prevent its spread from Luzon to other regions, divided by sea (such as Negros Occidental, in the northwestern half of the large island of Negros), are commendable. Unfortunately, their chances of success are arguable in view of the structure of the pig industry, the extremely high number of smallholders with backyard husbandry, and swill feeding.

The Philippines is an archipelagic country that consists of about 7641 islands that are categorized broadly under 3 main geographical divisions from north to south: Luzon, Visayas and Mindanao. The province Negros Occidental, mentioned above, is situated within the Western Visayas (see map at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippines#Administrative_divisions).

Subscribers are encouraged to visit Mod.CRD's commentary in ProMED-mail's posting 20190910.6666730. - Mod.AS

